WEBVTT

00:06.506 --> 00:08.425
[opening theme music playing]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

00:53.762 --> 00:55.138
[somber music playing]

00:55.221 --> 01:01.019
JULY 2014

01:01.102 --> 01:03.313
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

01:03.396 --> 01:05.106
5:09 A.M.

01:13.114 --> 01:15.742
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

01:18.244 --> 01:23.833
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

01:27.462 --> 01:28.379
Hello.

01:32.675 --> 01:34.010
Hui-seo, you think can you walk?

01:35.220 --> 01:36.095
Yeah.

01:37.931 --> 01:38.765
[groans]

01:39.474 --> 01:40.683
[Hui-seo groans]

01:41.643 --> 01:42.894
Hui-seo, get on my back.

01:44.437 --> 01:46.606
Hui-seo, try to stand. You can do it.

01:46.689 --> 01:49.150
-Don't trouble your brother.
-Ma'am, it's fine.

01:49.234 --> 01:50.777
[woman sighs]

01:51.861 --> 01:53.029
Hui-seo.

01:53.113 --> 01:55.573
Okay. One, two, three.

01:55.657 --> 01:57.075
[grunts]

01:57.158 --> 01:59.160
[lighthearted music playing]

02:02.664 --> 02:04.040
Are you feeling okay?

02:04.124 --> 02:05.959
[train door alarm beeping]

02:11.923 --> 02:12.841
[Tae-seo] Sorry.

02:16.845 --> 02:17.887
You okay?

02:26.980 --> 02:33.695
STILL SHINING

02:40.118 --> 02:42.954
[bus brake hissing]

02:44.789 --> 02:45.915
You think you can you walk?

02:47.000 --> 02:47.959
Goodness.

02:48.626 --> 02:50.879
[Hui-seo] Grandma,
could you move back a bit?

02:50.962 --> 02:51.921
I'll come down.

02:52.839 --> 02:54.966
Come over here. He said he can manage.

02:57.385 --> 02:59.053
[Hui-seo grunts]

02:59.637 --> 03:00.889
[chuckles]

03:00.972 --> 03:03.016
-I'm pretty good, right?
-Yes, well done.

03:03.099 --> 03:05.768
I told you I'm all better now.
You don't have to worry about me.

03:05.852 --> 03:07.562
I'm very proud of you.

03:08.688 --> 03:10.106
Goodness. Hi, Tae-seo.

03:10.857 --> 03:12.984
-It's good to see you.
-Have you been well?

03:13.067 --> 03:15.862
CONGRATULATIONS ON YOUR GRADUATION

03:17.906 --> 03:18.740
[music fades]

03:19.449 --> 03:20.992
[Hui-seo] My medical report?

03:21.075 --> 03:23.411
You might not be ready for school
when classes start,

03:24.162 --> 03:25.204
so I'll submit it for you.

03:25.997 --> 03:27.999
I'm going to school, even if I'm hurt.

03:28.082 --> 03:30.043
You came all the way here for my sake.

03:30.126 --> 03:32.045
I'm not a kid. I can manage just fine.

03:33.129 --> 03:35.089
I can just take Bus 19 at the bus stop.

03:38.551 --> 03:39.385
Ugh.

03:40.637 --> 03:42.138
Hey, the bus stop! [grunts]

03:42.222 --> 03:43.139
Grandpa!

03:43.806 --> 03:45.433
Stop! Tae-seo's going to school.

03:47.936 --> 03:51.940
Right, your grandfather was worried
that Hui-seo would have trouble walking.

03:52.023 --> 03:55.026
He can walk fine on crutches,
and I'll go with him to and from school.

03:55.735 --> 03:57.987
I saw him playing soccer last summer.

03:58.655 --> 04:00.240
I also talked with your father.

04:01.282 --> 04:03.576
My parents both worked,

04:03.660 --> 04:05.578
so Hui-seo always came here
during vacation.

04:06.287 --> 04:08.456
Right. Well, you hang in there too.

04:08.539 --> 04:11.960
[inhales deeply] The local
elementary school closed last year,

04:12.043 --> 04:14.087
and there's been talk
about us closing too.

04:14.629 --> 04:17.924
[clicks tongue] But Hui-seo
should be able to graduate. Mmm.

04:18.007 --> 04:19.092
We don't get any transfers.

04:19.175 --> 04:20.885
You're the first in five years.

04:20.969 --> 04:21.970
[Tae-seo] I see.

04:22.053 --> 04:22.971
So…

04:23.554 --> 04:25.473
Did my documents and transcripts arrive?

04:26.099 --> 04:27.684
[Jeong-su] I'm looking for them now.

04:27.767 --> 04:29.018
Yes, they're all here.

04:29.102 --> 04:32.188
[inhales sharply] And I see
this is your second transfer this year.

04:33.231 --> 04:35.441
Why didn't you just come straight here?

04:35.525 --> 04:38.027
My aunt said
I had to go to college in Seoul.

04:38.111 --> 04:40.196
-Living in Seoul won't guarantee that.
-[chuckles]

04:40.280 --> 04:41.823
You didn't cause trouble there, right?

04:41.906 --> 04:43.199
No, of course not.

04:43.283 --> 04:45.618
Hui-seo found it hard adjusting to Seoul.

04:45.702 --> 04:46.703
Why?

04:47.704 --> 04:49.455
He was being bullied.

04:49.539 --> 04:53.042
[Jeong-su] God, those awful punks.
Doing that to someone who's hurt…

04:53.126 --> 04:56.379
I'll keep an eye on him,
so don't worry too much.

04:56.462 --> 05:01.301
With us, all the kids aiming for college
have transferred to schools in the city.

05:01.384 --> 05:04.220
The rest who remain here
help out with their family businesses,

05:04.304 --> 05:05.972
so they have no pressure to study.

05:06.055 --> 05:10.059
Anyway, let's make sure
you get your high school diploma here.

05:10.143 --> 05:11.311
Mmm.

05:11.394 --> 05:12.603
And no need to buy a uniform.

05:14.105 --> 05:16.274
We have some
that our graduates handed down.

05:16.357 --> 05:17.900
You should grab Hui-seo's as well.

05:17.984 --> 05:18.901
Okay.

05:19.610 --> 05:23.114
This one's for winter. The summer ones
are in front of the library upstairs.

05:23.656 --> 05:25.408
They're usually inside the library,

05:25.491 --> 05:26.826
but there's a kid named Mo Eun-a.

05:26.909 --> 05:29.537
She's doing independent study there,
so we moved them outside.

05:30.121 --> 05:31.873
She's the transfer from five years ago.

05:42.800 --> 05:47.764
LIBRARY

05:56.773 --> 05:58.691
[slow piano music playing]

06:17.627 --> 06:19.087
UNIFORM DONATION BOX (SUMMER)

06:20.963 --> 06:22.590
-[door slides open]
-[music fades]

06:24.133 --> 06:26.177
[door slides shut]

06:26.969 --> 06:28.805
Hey, what on earth is this?

06:29.764 --> 06:32.100
Oh. It got crumpled in my bag.

06:32.183 --> 06:34.227
They're my mock exam scores
from March and June.

06:34.310 --> 06:36.312
I thought you may need them
for college counseling.

06:36.395 --> 06:38.856
No, the crumpling isn't the issue.
Look at this.

06:39.524 --> 06:41.859
Top-ranked student multiple times,
all 99s for grades,

06:41.943 --> 06:44.529
and in the highest percentile
in all major subjects.

06:44.612 --> 06:47.949
Geez, with these grades,
you can take your pick of med schools!

06:48.032 --> 06:51.494
You should have this framed,
not shoved into your bag.

06:52.829 --> 06:53.913
Gosh, you're…

06:54.747 --> 06:55.665
Wow!

06:58.167 --> 06:59.335
Gosh…

06:59.418 --> 07:01.420
[fan whirring]

07:09.804 --> 07:12.390
[insects trilling]

07:29.490 --> 07:31.492
[high-pitched ringing]

07:35.496 --> 07:36.330
[ringing stops]

07:41.502 --> 07:43.504
[insects trilling]

07:43.588 --> 07:45.882
[slow piano music playing]

07:56.726 --> 07:57.727
[sighs]

08:26.464 --> 08:28.174
Your desk didn't arrive.

08:28.257 --> 08:30.259
I told them a while ago.

08:31.552 --> 08:33.346
Goodness, what a mess.

08:37.308 --> 08:41.145
YEON CHANG-SIK

08:45.775 --> 08:46.901
Tae-seo's here.

08:48.361 --> 08:50.404
Gosh, good job finding your way here!

08:51.322 --> 08:52.865
But we have a problem.

08:52.949 --> 08:54.492
Your desk didn't arrive.

08:54.575 --> 08:55.743
I already told him.

08:56.744 --> 08:59.622
We should've made sure it arrived today.

09:00.706 --> 09:01.999
It's okay, Grandma.

09:02.083 --> 09:05.294
[chuckles] Right,
I'll make sure to tell them tomorrow.

09:05.378 --> 09:08.589
Why did you have to throw out
his father's desk? [inhales sharply]

09:09.423 --> 09:11.217
Why are you talking about his father?

09:11.300 --> 09:14.387
[Hwa-sun] I'm just saying you could've
thrown it out after the new one came.

09:14.470 --> 09:15.304
[Chang-sik grunts]

09:32.363 --> 09:34.198
[sentimental music playing]

10:06.606 --> 10:07.648
[grunts]

10:18.576 --> 10:19.577
[music fades]

10:19.660 --> 10:21.370
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
CLASS 3-1

10:23.664 --> 10:25.416
[clattering]

10:27.501 --> 10:29.545
[clattering continues]

10:35.926 --> 10:36.927
[exhales heavily]

10:56.781 --> 10:59.950
The lights didn't even come on
since it's summer break, so I made a fuss.

11:00.743 --> 11:03.579
I heard they make you do independent study
until 10:00 p.m. in Seoul,

11:03.663 --> 11:06.040
so the least they could do
is help me study here.

11:06.791 --> 11:10.211
So now, just the library has power,
and I can use the fans.

11:12.672 --> 11:13.756
Turn that one on.

11:19.845 --> 11:21.097
Which bus did you take?

11:22.640 --> 11:23.682
The 6:12 a.m. bus.

11:24.558 --> 11:25.476
That's the first one.

11:29.355 --> 11:30.481
Sit wherever you like.

11:49.041 --> 11:50.876
You can switch into study mode right away?

11:53.337 --> 11:55.631
I need to warm up first. Don't mind me.

11:57.425 --> 11:58.759
[zipper unzips]

12:09.854 --> 12:10.896
Let me say one thing.

12:11.480 --> 12:12.690
Just this. I promise.

12:14.233 --> 12:16.402
Go on. [clears throat]

12:16.986 --> 12:19.947
I suddenly have time
to spend on myself now.

12:20.990 --> 12:22.491
I was taking care of my dad…

12:25.202 --> 12:26.745
But I won't get into that.

12:27.788 --> 12:29.832
I just didn't want to waste this time,

12:29.915 --> 12:31.834
so I decided to study.

12:31.917 --> 12:34.962
I wasn't planning on going to college,
but I think I will.

12:35.671 --> 12:37.214
I don't know what I want to become,

12:37.298 --> 12:38.841
but I'll figure it out as I go.

12:39.758 --> 12:42.344
I know it won't change much,
but I'm giving it a go.

12:42.428 --> 12:45.222
What I mean is,
I was never big on studying.

12:46.557 --> 12:48.559
[amusing music playing]

12:49.059 --> 12:50.227
Just saying.

12:51.020 --> 12:51.937
Right.

12:52.563 --> 12:54.106
So my point was,

12:54.190 --> 12:55.900
that's why I need to warm up.

12:56.567 --> 12:57.818
I move around, so bear with me.

12:57.902 --> 12:59.487
Okay, do as you please.

13:06.285 --> 13:07.119
The Wi-Fi password.

13:07.203 --> 13:09.872
-[scoffs]
-I downloaded some online lectures,

13:09.955 --> 13:12.124
so I'll lend you my USB if you need them.

13:12.833 --> 13:13.751
I'm fine.

13:19.215 --> 13:21.884
Blue is for seniors, green for juniors,
and sophomores are…

13:22.635 --> 13:23.719
Maybe yellow?

13:25.846 --> 13:27.223
YEONWOO HIGH SCHOOL
MO EUN-A

13:34.063 --> 13:36.482
You're Yeon Tae-seo.
Hui-seo's older brother.

13:36.565 --> 13:38.025
We call your place "Hui-seo's."

13:39.777 --> 13:40.778
[music fades]

13:42.988 --> 13:44.490
[paper rustles]

13:56.835 --> 13:58.254
[paper rustles]

14:03.092 --> 14:04.009
Sorry.

14:08.097 --> 14:10.099
[amusing music playing]

14:29.159 --> 14:30.911
[door slides open]

14:40.462 --> 14:41.881
[grunts]

14:43.549 --> 14:44.508
-[sighs]
-[music fades]

14:57.605 --> 14:59.565
[Eun-a in English] "Facilitate."

15:01.108 --> 15:03.777
"Facilitate."

15:03.861 --> 15:05.070
[amusing music playing]

15:05.154 --> 15:10.075
"Facilitate."

15:10.659 --> 15:16.206
"Facilitate."

15:17.917 --> 15:24.131
"FASILITAT…"

15:25.174 --> 15:27.301
[in Korean] The men's room
is to the right.

15:28.802 --> 15:30.054
[in English] "F…"

15:35.976 --> 15:36.977
[music fades]

15:39.813 --> 15:40.814
[exhales heavily]

15:41.523 --> 15:43.025
[alarm beeping]

15:43.651 --> 15:44.735
[beeping stops]

15:48.656 --> 15:50.032
What about lunch?

15:55.496 --> 15:56.997
That's definitely gone bad.

16:02.753 --> 16:03.796
[coughs]

16:04.588 --> 16:06.757
[coughing]

16:06.840 --> 16:08.759
TEACHERS' LOUNGE

16:09.635 --> 16:10.928
I'll restock the <i>ramyeon</i> I eat.

16:11.762 --> 16:15.015
Vacation's almost over anyway.
Two a day will last us just fine.

16:15.099 --> 16:18.018
I bought plenty in case anyone dropped by.

16:21.230 --> 16:22.231
Ah.

16:33.617 --> 16:34.618
For you and Hui-seo.

16:34.702 --> 16:37.329
Gym uniforms are valuable,
so upperclassmen never pass them on.

16:37.413 --> 16:38.956
They wear them forever.

16:39.039 --> 16:42.501
These are magic shorts.
They fit in middle school and as an adult.

16:43.335 --> 16:44.878
They always fit perfectly.

16:44.962 --> 16:47.089
It's amazing. They're so comfy too. Look!

16:47.172 --> 16:49.842
Hey! Come on, don't!

16:49.925 --> 16:51.010
You startled me.

16:52.469 --> 16:53.804
I'm just saying I'm wearing them.

16:55.014 --> 16:56.890
Thanks for these.

16:58.183 --> 16:59.268
Ah.

16:59.351 --> 17:00.936
[whimsical music playing]

17:02.438 --> 17:04.273
Your grandma's homemade kimchi.

17:05.482 --> 17:06.942
This is really special.

17:09.570 --> 17:11.030
When we were trading items,

17:11.113 --> 17:14.450
we gave Hui-seo his soccer cleats
for your sesame oil and perilla oil.

17:14.533 --> 17:17.911
She thanked me every time she saw me
and then gave me a tub of kimchi.

17:17.995 --> 17:20.789
This kimchi is what my dad and I
treasure the most.

17:20.873 --> 17:22.082
Hui-seo's soccer cleats?

17:22.166 --> 17:23.792
Yeah, last fall.

17:23.876 --> 17:25.753
You were the one who bought them?

17:25.836 --> 17:27.588
I told you it was a trade.

17:27.671 --> 17:30.632
Your grandma would never know
what to get Hui-seo whenever he visited.

17:30.716 --> 17:34.845
The shoe bag and Park Ji-sung's jersey.
They were all my idea.

17:34.928 --> 17:37.389
She asks me for help every year.
Just for Hui-seo's gifts.

17:38.265 --> 17:39.725
She said you didn't want any.

17:43.103 --> 17:44.188
Eat up.

17:54.698 --> 17:55.699
[music fades]

17:55.783 --> 17:57.409
[Eun-a] Time to catch the bus.

17:58.869 --> 18:01.580
If you miss this one,
the next one comes in an hour and a half.

18:06.376 --> 18:07.461
Are you coming tomorrow?

18:07.544 --> 18:09.588
I'm in charge of opening
and closing the library.

18:09.671 --> 18:11.381
If you take the 6:50 bus, I'll be here--

18:11.465 --> 18:12.591
Don't worry about me.

18:15.511 --> 18:18.430
I don't know if I'm coming tomorrow yet,
so don't worry about me.

18:20.182 --> 18:21.100
Fine.

18:28.482 --> 18:29.399
Aren't you going?

18:30.150 --> 18:31.068
I came on my bike.

18:34.571 --> 18:36.490
I waited so I could tell you the bus time.

18:48.836 --> 18:50.045
[bike bell rings]

18:50.129 --> 18:51.672
Run! You'll miss the bus.

18:52.881 --> 18:54.716
You can see fireflies even in the fall!

19:08.522 --> 19:11.108
[woman] <i>Hui-seo, I'm cold. Let's go home.</i>

19:11.984 --> 19:13.777
[man] <i>Yeon Hui-seo, listen to your mother.</i>

19:15.195 --> 19:16.572
We're going on ahead.

19:16.655 --> 19:18.740
[heartwarming music playing]

19:18.824 --> 19:22.286
Come on!
That bug's not around in the fall.

19:23.370 --> 19:25.455
They all die after the summer.

19:25.539 --> 19:26.373
Hurry up.

19:27.291 --> 19:28.750
Hey, it's a firefly!

19:30.043 --> 19:31.420
Where?

19:32.462 --> 19:33.964
Hey, it really is a firefly!

19:35.090 --> 19:38.468
[grunts] There's so many! Grab them!

19:38.552 --> 19:39.386
[Tae-seo] Dad!

19:39.469 --> 19:41.346
[Tae-seo's mom]
Where's Hui-seo? Isn't he coming?

19:41.430 --> 19:43.807
[Tae-seo] I don't know.
He's catching fireflies.

19:43.891 --> 19:46.059
[Tae-seo's dad] We grew up
eating fireflies back in the day.

19:46.143 --> 19:47.895
-[Tae-seo's mom] Seriously?
-[Tae-seo] You're lying.

19:47.978 --> 19:50.272
-You ate them?
-Eating a firefly makes you electric.

19:50.355 --> 19:51.315
[Tae-seo's mom] Don't be silly.

19:51.398 --> 19:53.150
-[Tae-seo] Dad is so unfunny.
-[Tae-seo's mom] Yeah.

19:59.448 --> 20:00.365
[bike bell rings]

20:23.680 --> 20:24.681
[music ends]

20:24.765 --> 20:26.808
Does your grandpa not know
how big you are now?

20:26.892 --> 20:28.769
He really is clueless.

20:29.561 --> 20:31.605
It's okay.

20:31.688 --> 20:32.856
It's nice and sturdy.

20:32.940 --> 20:35.067
Tae-seo can study anywhere.

20:35.150 --> 20:36.860
As long as he can sit, it's fine.

20:36.944 --> 20:38.612
Did you walk a bit today?

20:38.695 --> 20:40.155
Of course.

20:40.239 --> 20:44.076
I'm fine. Look. I'll be flying around
once the cast comes off.

20:44.159 --> 20:45.118
Just you wait and see.

20:45.702 --> 20:48.914
[Hwa-sun] What should I pack
for your lunch to take to school tomorrow?

20:48.997 --> 20:52.000
He's not going to school, Grandma.
He has a desk now.

20:52.084 --> 20:52.918
Ah…

20:53.001 --> 20:55.254
[Hui-seo] I want <i>bibim-guksu</i>
for lunch tomorrow.

20:55.337 --> 20:57.339
-[Hwa-sun] Sounds great.
-[Hui-seo] I'm craving it.

21:20.862 --> 21:22.406
[Eun-a] This is a bit hard to open.

21:23.198 --> 21:25.450
[lock rattling]

21:25.534 --> 21:28.495
-Did you see me last Chuseok?
-I saw you every year.

21:28.578 --> 21:31.248
You stopped coming
in the summer after eighth grade.

21:32.457 --> 21:35.585
Even during Chuseok, you only stayed
briefly because you had to study.

21:37.004 --> 21:39.423
What happened? You acted like
you weren't coming today.

21:39.506 --> 21:41.091
I have to study.

21:43.468 --> 21:45.053
Since when have you known me?

21:45.804 --> 21:49.182
I moved here five years ago, so since
your last summer visit five years ago.

21:50.642 --> 21:52.269
Why the sudden interest?

21:54.187 --> 21:56.606
So you were nice to me
because you knew me.

21:57.941 --> 21:59.735
I'm just saying that I get it now.

22:03.572 --> 22:06.450
If you pick a spot and hide the key,
I'll open up if I arrive early.

22:07.576 --> 22:08.535
No.

22:08.618 --> 22:11.872
The school entrusted it to me,
so I need to open and close up.

22:11.955 --> 22:14.207
You can show up whenever and just study.

22:14.291 --> 22:15.917
The key is my responsibility.

22:19.129 --> 22:20.255
What?

22:21.048 --> 22:22.299
I didn't say anything.

22:24.259 --> 22:25.135
[Eun-a scoffs]

22:26.053 --> 22:28.847
You don't have to know someone
to be nice to them.

22:28.930 --> 22:30.307
We're both just country kids here.

22:33.769 --> 22:34.978
Hmm.

22:35.812 --> 22:37.856
It's going to be another hot day today.

22:40.484 --> 22:42.486
[lighthearted music playing]

23:08.303 --> 23:09.387
Do you want to use this?

23:10.764 --> 23:12.474
Yeah, thanks.

23:12.557 --> 23:13.725
[Tae-seo clears throat]

23:15.435 --> 23:16.436
[exhales heavily]

23:16.978 --> 23:17.813
[sniffles]

23:19.189 --> 23:20.524
[sighs]

23:28.698 --> 23:29.574
[exhales heavily]

23:35.455 --> 23:37.249
-What?
-What?

23:39.042 --> 23:40.168
It looks good on you.

23:41.920 --> 23:43.046
[Tae-seo] Mmm.

23:44.172 --> 23:45.048
[Eun-a chuckles]

23:48.093 --> 23:49.094
[music ends]

23:49.177 --> 23:50.971
Where's your bike?

23:51.054 --> 23:52.180
I took the bus today.

23:52.764 --> 23:54.015
I brought my bike today.

23:55.725 --> 23:58.728
Well, I just thought I'd ride with you
and get a little exercise.

24:00.730 --> 24:01.815
Then, go exercise.

24:01.898 --> 24:03.066
-Mmm.
-[in English] Bye.

24:21.001 --> 24:22.502
[bus buzzer beeps]

24:35.348 --> 24:36.808
[bus brake hisses]

24:37.601 --> 24:39.019
[in Korean] I'm getting off.

24:45.150 --> 24:46.526
[upbeat music playing]

24:55.493 --> 24:59.206
-[door alarm beeps]
-Sir, quickly! Hurry!

25:13.178 --> 25:14.554
[bus buzzer beeps]

25:38.912 --> 25:40.622
[Eun-a panting]

25:44.167 --> 25:45.168
[music ends]

25:48.672 --> 25:49.714
[scoffs]

25:49.798 --> 25:51.091
I'm not getting on.

25:51.174 --> 25:52.842
Don't you dare try to give me a ride.

25:56.096 --> 25:58.098
[bike bell ringing]

26:02.018 --> 26:03.228
Are you serious?

26:08.483 --> 26:09.317
[brake squeaks]

26:10.402 --> 26:12.153
[panting]

26:25.542 --> 26:26.501
[bike bell rings]

26:30.463 --> 26:32.465
[pleasant music playing]

27:03.079 --> 27:04.080
[music fades]

27:09.461 --> 27:10.628
[Tae-seo] What's wrong?

27:17.552 --> 27:18.511
Oh.

27:20.096 --> 27:22.098
[soft romantic music playing]

27:32.150 --> 27:34.569
-[Eun-a] The weather's nice.
-[Tae-seo] Yeah.

27:37.989 --> 27:39.616
[Eun-a] Are you getting tired?

27:39.699 --> 27:40.533
[Tae-seo] No.

27:41.618 --> 27:42.452
[Eun-a] Are you hot?

27:43.161 --> 27:44.162
[Tae-seo] No.

27:45.288 --> 27:47.457
-[Eun-a] Do you want to eat ice cream?
-[Tae-seo] No.

27:49.000 --> 27:49.834
Yeah.

28:18.655 --> 28:19.864
Try throwing it farther.

28:21.199 --> 28:22.033
[grunts]

28:27.455 --> 28:28.790
Hey, the bus is coming.

28:30.208 --> 28:31.626
Your bag!

28:32.210 --> 28:33.461
Your bag.

28:48.351 --> 28:52.689
MO EUN-A

28:53.857 --> 28:54.983
YEON TAE-SEO

29:10.373 --> 29:12.584
[sighs softly] It's really hot.

29:33.313 --> 29:34.314
[music ends]

29:34.397 --> 29:36.566
[dog barking in distance]

29:36.649 --> 29:37.734
Hello.

29:48.411 --> 29:50.955
[man 1 in English]
Thank you so much for inviting us.

29:51.039 --> 29:52.457
[woman 1] I want to take a photo.

29:52.540 --> 29:55.043
[man 1] Let's take a picture of this one.
It looks amazing.

29:55.126 --> 29:57.003
-Oh, what is this?
-[all exclaiming]

29:57.086 --> 29:59.756
-[female guests] What is this?
-This is your dessert.

30:00.340 --> 30:02.842
-[So-hyeon in Korean] <i>Husik.</i>
-[guests] <i>Husik?</i>

30:02.926 --> 30:03.843
[in English] Waxy corn.

30:03.927 --> 30:05.929
[guests] Waxy corn.

30:06.012 --> 30:07.847
[So-hyeon in Korean]
That name doesn't feel right.

30:07.931 --> 30:09.140
<i>Chal-oksusu.</i>

30:09.224 --> 30:11.935
-[man 2] <i>Chal-oksoso.</i>
-[woman 2] <i>Oksusu.</i>

30:12.018 --> 30:14.270
<i>-Oksosu?</i>
-[man 2] <i>Susu.</i>

30:14.354 --> 30:15.980
<i>-Susu.</i>
-[woman 2] <i>Oksusu.</i>

30:16.064 --> 30:18.483
-[laughter]
-[woman 2] <i>Oksusu.</i>

30:18.566 --> 30:19.776
[man 1 in English] This is nice!

30:19.859 --> 30:22.237
-[man 2] Is it sweet?
-[guests talking indistinctly]

30:22.320 --> 30:25.740
[So-hyeon] In Korean,
we call this <i>ssiganjang</i> salad.

30:32.997 --> 30:35.041
[in Korean] Thanks for making dinner.

30:35.124 --> 30:36.543
Sure thing. Eat up.

30:38.044 --> 30:39.337
Did So-hyeon leave?

30:40.672 --> 30:43.550
Yeah, she went to Seoul
with the guests from Hawaii.

30:47.053 --> 30:48.763
You were drinking, weren't you?

30:50.139 --> 30:51.558
That's why I feel great.

30:53.101 --> 30:55.270
And then you'll feel worse tomorrow.

30:56.104 --> 30:58.314
No, I'll be fine.
You just focus on studying.

31:00.233 --> 31:02.694
Exactly. That's what
dads are supposed to do.

31:02.777 --> 31:04.696
Tell their children
to just study all the time.

31:04.779 --> 31:07.323
It feels great
that I finally get to hear that now.

31:08.533 --> 31:10.785
"What's the point of all that?
Just take it easy."

31:10.869 --> 31:12.328
That's what you always used to say.

31:14.372 --> 31:15.999
Just live freely.

31:16.082 --> 31:20.295
Try living in different countries
and search for what you want to do.

31:20.920 --> 31:22.255
As if you're on a journey.

31:26.301 --> 31:28.511
[sentimental music playing]

31:28.595 --> 31:29.429
Dad.

31:29.512 --> 31:33.391
I've been watching this kid who's been
through a lot but is pushing forward.

31:34.350 --> 31:35.602
It's really moving.

31:36.311 --> 31:38.021
-Someone your age?
-Yeah.

31:38.813 --> 31:41.774
-What a great kid.
-You're great too.

31:41.858 --> 31:42.942
You got all better for me.

31:43.026 --> 31:44.235
[chuckles]

31:45.194 --> 31:46.112
All right,

31:46.195 --> 31:47.864
I'll become an even greater dad.

31:49.824 --> 31:50.950
-Enough.
-[chuckles]

31:51.034 --> 31:52.160
[in English] Stop!

31:53.244 --> 31:54.537
[Eun-a] Mmm?

31:55.496 --> 31:56.998
[in Korean] All right, I'll stop.

31:57.665 --> 31:58.917
I need to be a great dad.

31:59.000 --> 32:00.293
[chuckles softly]

32:00.376 --> 32:02.378
[music continues]

32:20.980 --> 32:21.814
[Hui-seo] Mmm.

32:35.912 --> 32:36.746
[Hui-seo] Mom…

32:36.829 --> 32:37.664
[music fades]

32:39.749 --> 32:40.583
[sighs softly]

32:41.334 --> 32:42.377
[Hui-seo] Mom.

32:42.460 --> 32:44.462
[rain pattering]

32:51.302 --> 32:52.387
[sighs]

33:05.400 --> 33:06.901
Any reservations today?

33:08.861 --> 33:09.696
No.

33:12.073 --> 33:13.741
I guess no energy either.

33:13.825 --> 33:18.079
Your stomach's probably empty,
so take this with the stomach medicine.

33:19.706 --> 33:22.834
I'm just feeling a little weak
because I threw up this morning.

33:27.130 --> 33:29.173
Go to school. Go study.

33:31.926 --> 33:34.554
Just give me five minutes, Dad.
Take the medicine.

33:34.637 --> 33:35.555
Okay?

33:48.359 --> 33:49.944
[pleasant music playing]

33:51.863 --> 33:53.031
Yeon Tae-seo!

34:05.877 --> 34:06.961
Here.

34:07.670 --> 34:10.548
-Aren't you coming to school?
-I will. Wait for me.

34:21.768 --> 34:22.769
[music fades]

34:29.984 --> 34:32.570
Dad? Dad!

34:33.780 --> 34:35.907
Dad? [pants]

34:38.618 --> 34:39.702
Dad!

34:39.786 --> 34:41.370
[panting]

34:44.290 --> 34:45.249
[sighs in relief]

34:54.342 --> 34:55.802
[door rattling]

35:04.685 --> 35:06.896
[pensive music playing]

35:27.375 --> 35:28.209
[sighs]

35:34.966 --> 35:36.717
[footsteps approaching]

35:43.307 --> 35:44.308
[music fades]

35:49.814 --> 35:51.023
[sighs softly]

36:00.992 --> 36:02.160
[Eun-a] Nothing bad happened.

36:02.243 --> 36:04.078
I just freaked out for no reason.

36:05.580 --> 36:06.581
I can't hear you.

36:08.332 --> 36:09.709
Sometimes I can't hear your voice.

36:09.792 --> 36:11.836
Tell me what you just said.

36:14.338 --> 36:17.466
I was acting stupid,
but now, I feel calmer after seeing you.

36:17.550 --> 36:20.553
Seeing you makes me feel at ease.

36:54.629 --> 36:56.631
[exhales heavily]

37:03.471 --> 37:05.932
[Eun-a] <i>So-hyeon, what time</i>
<i>are you coming today?</i>

37:11.604 --> 37:12.813
[cell phone buzzes]

37:15.107 --> 37:16.984
[So-hyeon] <i>I won't be coming today.</i>

37:24.617 --> 37:25.493
Look at me.

37:28.663 --> 37:29.580
Look.

37:29.664 --> 37:31.082
You said it helps.

37:33.125 --> 37:35.127
[heart-fluttering music playing]

37:44.095 --> 37:45.429
I know it helps.

37:46.013 --> 37:47.723
But I need to go home right now.

37:48.516 --> 37:50.768
I'll only get in the way
of your studying like this.

37:50.851 --> 37:51.894
It's not good for you.

37:55.940 --> 37:57.233
No, don't.

38:05.074 --> 38:06.575
Go back to studying.

38:27.096 --> 38:28.097
[sighs softly]

38:32.935 --> 38:34.228
[sighs]

38:40.026 --> 38:40.860
[music fades]

38:42.403 --> 38:43.612
[women talking indistinctly]

38:44.822 --> 38:47.283
-Tae-seo! Goodness.
-Grandma.

38:47.366 --> 38:51.203
I came here to buy some mosquito coils.
Let's go home together.

38:51.287 --> 38:55.833
Goodness, who's this handsome young man?

38:55.916 --> 38:57.084
-[chuckles]
-Hello.

38:58.252 --> 39:00.713
-Come eat with us. Come, come.
-All right.

39:00.796 --> 39:01.714
I'll carry that.

39:02.673 --> 39:04.258
Go say hello to everyone.

39:24.820 --> 39:26.447
LIBRARY

39:30.951 --> 39:32.953
[footsteps approaching]

39:40.753 --> 39:42.755
[slow music playing]

40:08.030 --> 40:10.866
[door rattling]

40:10.950 --> 40:11.951
[music fades]

40:15.704 --> 40:16.789
[Eun-a] Name tags?

40:20.376 --> 40:22.044
IM A-SOL
IM JI-SOL

40:28.134 --> 40:29.343
What are these?

40:37.810 --> 40:41.439
I guess it's true that kids in Seoul
say they like someone by giving name tags.

40:41.522 --> 40:44.316
When did they put those in there?
I had no idea.

40:44.400 --> 40:48.946
Im Ji-sol, Kim Eun-su, Im A-sol.
A lot of girls with the last name "Im."

40:49.697 --> 40:51.615
[scoffs] I have no idea.

40:52.283 --> 40:53.200
No idea about what?

40:54.910 --> 40:55.911
Who's the prettiest?

40:57.163 --> 40:58.205
I don't know.

40:58.873 --> 41:02.084
I know who Im Ji-sol is,
but Hyeong-seok's the one who liked her.

41:02.168 --> 41:03.586
-So you do know.
-[scoffs]

41:03.669 --> 41:06.422
Well, she was pretty famous.
She did well in school.

41:06.505 --> 41:07.423
So?

41:08.924 --> 41:09.758
I have no idea.

41:13.387 --> 41:15.556
-This is bad.
-[Tae-seo] What is?

41:16.307 --> 41:18.225
It's stuck in my head.

41:19.226 --> 41:21.103
I memorized their names.

41:21.187 --> 41:23.481
[sighs] It's not like that.

41:23.564 --> 41:25.357
I really had no idea
they put those in there.

41:25.441 --> 41:26.609
How could you not know?

41:30.070 --> 41:31.363
When you're always tense,

41:32.031 --> 41:34.742
you only see and hear
what's right in front of you.

41:37.828 --> 41:39.330
Are you still tense right now?

41:42.458 --> 41:44.960
Just explain what happened yesterday.
I was really worried.

41:50.174 --> 41:52.885
I told you before
that I was taking care of my dad.

41:54.428 --> 41:56.138
He had severe depression.

41:56.889 --> 41:58.224
He even attempted suicide.

42:01.936 --> 42:05.105
When? Did you see it happen?

42:05.189 --> 42:06.565
I only saw him being taken away.

42:07.233 --> 42:09.610
He got divorced and left his job.

42:09.693 --> 42:12.029
We came nearby here on a trip.

42:12.112 --> 42:15.074
He fell in love with the marshes,
and we moved in five years ago.

42:15.783 --> 42:16.992
It happened that year.

42:17.910 --> 42:20.829
Ever since then, I get really anxious
when he's by himself.

42:21.622 --> 42:24.833
Mmm… But he got a new job
just before summer break

42:24.917 --> 42:26.627
and also started seeing someone.

42:26.710 --> 42:28.546
If you ask me,
dating made a big difference.

42:28.629 --> 42:31.840
My dad told me to stop hovering around him
and go do what I want.

42:32.424 --> 42:34.760
Before that,
I hadn't even considered college.

42:34.843 --> 42:36.720
I was going to stay and help him out.

42:37.680 --> 42:38.806
So for the first time ever,

42:38.889 --> 42:42.184
I considered a different future
and started studying on my own.

42:43.269 --> 42:45.062
And then, Yeon Tae-seo appeared.

42:45.980 --> 42:48.232
-The one Im A-sol likes.
-[coughing]

42:49.149 --> 42:50.901
[chuckles] I'll stop. Sorry.

42:52.403 --> 42:53.529
Cut it out.

42:56.448 --> 43:00.786
Yesterday's situation happened
because my dad had changed, but I hadn't.

43:00.869 --> 43:02.830
My dad told me

43:03.747 --> 43:06.000
he thought he'd live with anxiety forever,

43:06.750 --> 43:09.545
but once he saw how trivial it really was,
the anxiety vanished.

43:11.088 --> 43:13.549
And that's exactly
what I experienced yesterday.

43:14.174 --> 43:16.135
I went home, and nothing had happened.

43:26.979 --> 43:29.106
I bet you're not considering
any local universities.

43:29.732 --> 43:31.358
And I'd never get into one in Seoul.

43:31.442 --> 43:32.443
We'll end up apart.

43:33.193 --> 43:35.446
-You're going to Seoul, right?
-Yeah.

43:36.196 --> 43:38.741
My grandparents and Hui-seo
are precious to me,

43:38.824 --> 43:40.534
so I want to help them from a distance.

43:41.327 --> 43:43.621
When I'm too close, I burn out easily.

43:44.830 --> 43:46.999
[solemn music playing]

43:47.082 --> 43:49.251
They're precious,
so you'll distance yourself…

43:50.794 --> 43:54.256
I never considered distance
when thinking about the future.

44:16.278 --> 44:17.488
[Eun-a] It's different, right?

44:18.072 --> 44:19.948
It was still bright
at this hour yesterday.

44:20.032 --> 44:21.033
[music fades]

44:22.076 --> 44:23.327
You'll be going to Seoul.

44:24.620 --> 44:27.289
Where will I be
and what will I be doing next summer?

44:28.290 --> 44:31.794
When I thought about the future
all through summer break…

44:32.795 --> 44:35.923
[inhales deeply] I'd feel good one moment
and then overwhelmed.

44:36.006 --> 44:38.384
Then, I'd feel excited and then down…

44:39.510 --> 44:41.887
What thoughts made you
feel good and excited?

44:43.472 --> 44:46.350
Working like a cool professional
while wearing an employee badge.

44:46.433 --> 44:47.267
What kind of work?

44:47.351 --> 44:50.354
Uh… It keeps changing.

44:50.437 --> 44:51.772
It's a teacher one moment

44:51.855 --> 44:55.442
and then something like a therapist
or even a regular office worker.

44:56.235 --> 44:59.321
A place with a lot of employees
and a fancy desk.

44:59.405 --> 45:00.781
I like being around people,

45:00.864 --> 45:03.117
so I'll take the elevator
up to the 30th or 40th floor.

45:03.200 --> 45:04.535
And we'll all pour out for lunch.

45:05.744 --> 45:08.872
That sounds like
it'd be a huge, competitive company.

45:10.290 --> 45:12.709
[scoffs] I'm pretty good at English, okay?

45:13.460 --> 45:14.628
And I draw vegetables well.

45:14.711 --> 45:16.296
[lighthearted music playing]

45:24.513 --> 45:26.390
[Tae-seo] Yeah, you're pretty good.

45:27.349 --> 45:30.936
[scoffs] I know. I'm not saying
this will get me into art school.

45:32.354 --> 45:34.064
But I'll keep looking.

45:34.898 --> 45:36.650
Whatever I do, I want to give it my all.

45:36.733 --> 45:39.403
My dad keeps telling me
to just take it easy and live freely.

45:39.945 --> 45:40.988
But I don't want to.

45:41.071 --> 45:43.282
I'm going to hustle and give it my all.

45:48.245 --> 45:49.246
You?

45:49.746 --> 45:52.666
Hui-seo would always boast
and say you'd go to med school.

45:52.749 --> 45:54.877
That's what you aim for
if you want to study hard.

45:57.754 --> 46:01.216
I only did it to reassure my parents
who were living paycheck to paycheck.

46:02.050 --> 46:03.510
But now, I just feel restless.

46:03.594 --> 46:05.554
I just want to find a job
and start making money.

46:07.055 --> 46:09.600
I'll think about how to live my life
after that happens.

46:09.683 --> 46:13.187
Is it really possible
to think about it afterwards?

46:14.521 --> 46:16.607
If I focus on doing
what I can do right now,

46:16.690 --> 46:18.275
I'm sure I'll end up somewhere.

46:20.110 --> 46:21.445
You sound like a grown-up.

46:22.571 --> 46:25.407
[scoffs] Yeah, right.
I don't even have an ID card yet.

46:25.491 --> 46:27.367
You'll succeed no matter what you do.

46:28.035 --> 46:30.120
You're different from the rest.

46:30.204 --> 46:31.330
I just seem different.

46:32.122 --> 46:33.040
This was special.

46:35.959 --> 46:37.044
I mean our situation.

46:37.669 --> 46:40.088
It was just the two of us
studying in this huge school.

46:49.056 --> 46:50.265
You like people,

46:50.349 --> 46:52.809
you're good at English,
and you draw vegetables well.

46:52.893 --> 46:55.270
I know there's a job out there
you can give your all to.

46:57.564 --> 46:58.649
It'll work out

46:59.358 --> 47:00.859
in ways we never imagined.

47:03.153 --> 47:06.865
We'll know for sure what that is
once we become adults.

47:12.913 --> 47:14.081
[music fades]

47:14.164 --> 47:16.833
Where we'll be, what we'll do,
and with who…

47:23.382 --> 47:25.717
It feels like
we've been studying together all summer,

47:25.801 --> 47:26.969
but it's barely been a month.

47:27.052 --> 47:29.012
It was really nice studying with you.

47:29.096 --> 47:31.848
I felt more motivated
having someone else with me.

47:31.932 --> 47:33.392
I guess I like you.

47:44.736 --> 47:45.821
I'm all packed.

47:51.994 --> 47:53.328
[door slides open]

48:04.881 --> 48:07.217
[breathes deeply]

48:13.765 --> 48:15.767
[emotional music playing]

49:31.426 --> 49:32.427
[music fades]

49:32.511 --> 49:33.428
[students exclaiming]

49:33.512 --> 49:35.681
-It's been forever!
-[exclaims excitedly]

49:35.764 --> 49:37.265
[student] I want to go home!

49:38.225 --> 49:39.434
[grumbles]

49:45.607 --> 49:47.901
[indistinct chatter]

49:55.409 --> 49:57.452
[school bell ringing]

49:57.536 --> 49:58.370
[Jeong-su] Slow down.

49:58.954 --> 50:01.164
Hey, Kim Ji-min. Don't run!

50:01.957 --> 50:04.209
We don't offer physics
or a second foreign language,

50:04.292 --> 50:05.836
so you can study on your own.

50:06.795 --> 50:08.755
Just spend the day
studying at your own pace.

50:09.631 --> 50:10.882
Thank you, sir.

50:29.526 --> 50:31.570
MO EUN-A

50:31.653 --> 50:33.655
[sentimental music playing]

50:40.871 --> 50:42.164
[exclaims]

50:42.247 --> 50:43.582
Want to play basketball later?

50:43.665 --> 50:44.791
-What do you say?
-For a bet?

51:00.098 --> 51:06.188
SEPTEMBER

51:06.271 --> 51:07.314
[Tae-seo] <i>You're walking great.</i>

51:08.064 --> 51:09.274
Your Achilles is fully healed.

51:12.402 --> 51:14.738
Grandpa's waiting outside,
so take your time.

51:18.784 --> 51:20.535
Walking like this without a cast

51:21.453 --> 51:22.662
makes it feel real.

51:26.833 --> 51:28.293
I'm stuck like this for life, right?

51:30.045 --> 51:31.171
I'm scared, Tae-seo.

51:37.803 --> 51:39.805
[somber music playing]

51:46.061 --> 51:48.021
[Hui-seo] My right leg's fine,
so I can do it all.

51:48.104 --> 51:52.108
The doctor also said
this is nothing to worry about.

51:52.192 --> 51:54.361
-Right, Tae-seo?
-Yeah.

51:56.071 --> 51:59.699
When I'm all grown,
I'll be able to drive tractors and stuff.

52:00.826 --> 52:01.827
[inaudible]

52:01.910 --> 52:03.370
[high-pitched ringing]

52:03.453 --> 52:04.287
[ringing stops]

52:06.706 --> 52:07.791
[inaudible]

52:12.921 --> 52:16.675
I might be able to get rid of
the crutches soon.

52:16.758 --> 52:17.926
When I was walking earlier…

52:18.009 --> 52:21.721
OCTOBER

52:21.805 --> 52:22.889
[music fades]

52:22.973 --> 52:24.850
[man over PA] <i>Ladies and gentlemen.</i>

52:24.933 --> 52:26.560
<i>We will shortly arrive at Cheongnyangni…</i>

52:26.643 --> 52:29.104
[woman] We're almost at Seoul.
Let's wait at the door.

52:33.817 --> 52:34.985
Gosh, I'm sorry.

52:35.068 --> 52:37.070
[announcement over PA system continues]

52:52.377 --> 52:54.045
You didn't look back even once.

52:58.091 --> 52:59.926
-Where are you headed?
-Where you're going.

53:00.510 --> 53:03.221
I heard you got excused
to go to a college admissions seminar.

53:03.305 --> 53:05.056
I told them I was going as well.

53:07.726 --> 53:10.020
It feels like I haven't seen you in ages.

53:11.021 --> 53:12.147
I'm taking the subway.

53:13.356 --> 53:14.566
I'm on a tight schedule.

53:14.649 --> 53:16.735
I'm taking the subway too. What line?

53:16.818 --> 53:19.029
-Line 2.
-Gangbyeon Station…

53:19.112 --> 53:21.114
Isn't that close to Children's Grand Park?

53:21.197 --> 53:23.783
I think I went there once with my mom.

53:23.867 --> 53:24.910
All kids do at that age.

53:27.120 --> 53:29.664
But I don't know if it really happened
or if I imagined it.

53:29.748 --> 53:31.750
I'm not here to have fun.

53:35.879 --> 53:37.714
What line are you taking?
Do you know the way?

53:37.797 --> 53:39.132
Busy Yeon Tae-seo.

53:40.800 --> 53:41.718
Get going, then.

53:48.475 --> 53:50.477
[somber music playing]

53:55.941 --> 53:59.361
2015 HANGUK NATIONAL UNIVERSITY
ADMISSIONS INFORMATION SESSION

54:03.907 --> 54:05.408
I'm Yeon Tae-seo.

54:05.992 --> 54:07.994
[train door alarm beeping]

54:09.746 --> 54:11.623
[indistinct announcement over PA]

54:12.540 --> 54:14.000
[Eun-a] <i>So-hyeon, it's me.</i>

54:14.084 --> 54:16.127
<i>I'm on the subway right now.</i>

54:16.211 --> 54:18.922
<i>You live near Isu Station, right?</i>

54:19.005 --> 54:19.923
<i>Can I come?</i>

54:22.759 --> 54:23.677
[So-hyeon] <i>Of course.</i>

54:23.760 --> 54:26.221
<i>But take your time. I'm on my way as well.</i>

54:26.846 --> 54:30.183
<i>Come to Unit 610 at Space Inn</i>
<i>on 17 Isujungang-ro.</i>

54:30.266 --> 54:31.893
-[elevator dings]
-[music ends]

54:51.079 --> 54:53.206
[door lock beeping]

54:54.874 --> 54:57.002
-[So-hyeon] You're early.
-Yeah. Did you eat?

54:57.085 --> 54:57.919
[So-hyeon] Yeah.

55:01.715 --> 55:03.216
[chuckles] You're here.

55:05.802 --> 55:06.970
Who is he?

55:07.053 --> 55:08.179
Let's go inside.

55:11.057 --> 55:11.891
What's the matter?

55:11.975 --> 55:13.768
You're dating my dad.

55:14.936 --> 55:15.854
Oh…

55:17.814 --> 55:18.648
Eun-a.

55:18.732 --> 55:20.942
-What in the…
-You've got it wrong.

55:21.651 --> 55:22.902
-[scoffs]
-[inhales deeply]

55:22.986 --> 55:25.530
-You said you liked my dad.
-Yes.

55:26.114 --> 55:28.450
Liking someone doesn't always mean
you can date them.

55:29.075 --> 55:30.118
What kind of crap is that?

55:32.162 --> 55:34.998
Your dad won't date anyone.

55:36.583 --> 55:38.376
He's not interested in me.

55:45.675 --> 55:48.011
HANGUK NATIONAL UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

55:54.642 --> 55:55.643
[woman] You're all done.

55:55.727 --> 55:57.771
The results will be ready in an hour.

55:57.854 --> 55:58.938
You can come out now.

56:00.523 --> 56:06.696
MAEUM STUDY CENTER

56:08.198 --> 56:09.532
-[in English] Hi.
-[groans]

56:10.450 --> 56:12.327
[in Korean] Hurry and give it.
I have to go back now.

56:12.410 --> 56:14.329
Geez, you heartless punk.

56:14.829 --> 56:16.956
How did our teacher know
you were in Seoul?

56:17.040 --> 56:19.125
[sighs] He booked a seminar for me.

56:19.751 --> 56:21.419
You're always getting special treatment.

56:22.545 --> 56:24.172
I heard your mock exam score dipped.

56:24.255 --> 56:26.508
-He said this might cheer you up.
-What is it?

56:34.849 --> 56:39.437
FAMILY BACKGROUND SURVEY

56:42.065 --> 56:43.608
PARENTS' DESIRED CAREER PATH FOR CHILD

56:43.691 --> 56:45.360
[Tae-seo] <i>"Something safe and peaceful</i>

56:46.444 --> 56:49.864
<i>where he can make a living</i>
<i>without struggle."</i>

56:49.948 --> 56:51.950
[heartrending music playing]

56:53.701 --> 56:54.536
[sighs]

56:55.120 --> 56:57.163
[doctor] <i>There's no damage to the eardrum.</i>

56:57.789 --> 57:00.250
It's a temporary impairment
caused by exam stress,

57:00.333 --> 57:01.835
and your hearing may come and go.

57:02.460 --> 57:04.295
It should improve after the CSAT.

57:05.255 --> 57:07.382
When did the symptoms begin?

57:08.216 --> 57:10.885
March 3rd…

57:11.886 --> 57:13.721
That's right after starting
your senior year.

57:17.892 --> 57:19.352
No.

57:20.228 --> 57:21.062
So…

57:22.105 --> 57:25.108
It was after Hui-seo's entrance ceremony.

57:26.568 --> 57:29.696
They were going to buy him sneakers,
so Mom and Dad…

57:29.779 --> 57:31.781
[breathing shakily]

57:34.993 --> 57:36.161
They got in Dad's cab…

57:38.788 --> 57:40.623
and the three of them
got into an accident.

57:42.417 --> 57:43.835
Uh…

57:44.711 --> 57:46.212
[breath trembling]

57:46.296 --> 57:47.672
My parents passed away,

57:49.132 --> 57:50.383
and Hui-seo's leg…

57:51.342 --> 57:53.052
[breath trembling]

57:53.803 --> 57:54.679
His leg…

57:55.180 --> 57:57.640
[breathing heavily]

58:00.310 --> 58:01.186
Hui-seo's leg…

58:04.522 --> 58:05.607
[sobs]

58:14.449 --> 58:15.450
[music fades]

58:34.052 --> 58:36.054
-[cell phone vibrating]
-[sniffling]

58:41.184 --> 58:45.188
TAE-SEO

58:45.271 --> 58:46.606
[man over PA]
<i>The safety doors are closing.</i>

58:46.689 --> 58:49.317
-[Tae-seo] <i>Are you still in Seoul?</i>
-I'm not here to have fun either.

58:51.319 --> 58:54.614
-Where are you?
-[Eun-a] <i>It was a big leap for me.</i>

58:54.697 --> 58:56.282
<i>I didn't come here to have fun.</i>

58:56.908 --> 58:58.076
I tried distancing myself.

58:58.159 --> 59:00.328
I worked up the courage for the first time

59:01.538 --> 59:03.373
and tried stepping away from my dad.

59:04.457 --> 59:06.876
<i>I thought, "I might make it</i>
<i>if I follow Yeon Tae-seo."</i>

59:06.960 --> 59:09.420
I was able to come
because I thought I was going with you.

59:09.504 --> 59:11.506
[emotional music playing]

59:12.507 --> 59:13.550
Where are you?

59:15.134 --> 59:16.135
[sniffles]

59:17.220 --> 59:18.555
The stop after Isu Station.

59:19.264 --> 59:22.433
<i>-I have to get to Cheongnyangni Station.</i>
-Is it Dongjak Station?

59:24.769 --> 59:27.021
Yeah. [sobbing]

59:29.065 --> 59:31.442
<i>Dongjak Station…</i> [sobbing]

59:32.819 --> 59:34.904
[music continues]

01:00:15.153 --> 01:00:16.154
[music ends]

01:00:21.534 --> 01:00:22.535
The Hangang River.

01:00:23.161 --> 01:00:24.829
It's my first time seeing it.

01:00:26.539 --> 01:00:28.124
The Hangang River? Where?

01:00:29.500 --> 01:00:31.044
Over there. Look closely.

01:00:33.630 --> 01:00:34.714
I can't see anything.

01:00:40.762 --> 01:00:43.890
I'm seeing the Hangang River
for the first time with Yeon Tae-seo.

01:00:44.599 --> 01:00:46.601
[pleasant music plays]

01:01:01.949 --> 01:01:02.909
What's your deal?

01:01:02.992 --> 01:01:04.619
You're completely different now.

01:01:05.536 --> 01:01:07.538
You acted like you'd never see me again.

01:01:07.622 --> 01:01:09.374
-Earlier, I was--
-Not just earlier.

01:01:09.457 --> 01:01:11.876
Ever since summer break ended,
you ignored me and avoided--

01:01:11.959 --> 01:01:13.044
[shushes]

01:01:27.100 --> 01:01:28.601
The tension finally wore off.

01:01:31.229 --> 01:01:34.107
Today, just suddenly.

01:01:35.108 --> 01:01:36.234
I know that feeling.

01:01:36.859 --> 01:01:38.319
How it happens all of a sudden.

01:01:40.947 --> 01:01:44.701
I've felt sick since yesterday evening,
just thinking about leaving Yeonwoo.

01:01:45.493 --> 01:01:48.162
But the second I saw you
on the train earlier,

01:01:48.246 --> 01:01:51.082
all that anxiety disappeared suddenly.

01:01:52.917 --> 01:01:53.918
It's strange.

01:01:54.001 --> 01:01:56.504
I've been studying better because of you,

01:01:56.587 --> 01:01:58.840
and my grades have improved a little too.

01:01:59.424 --> 01:02:00.717
I also worked up my courage.

01:02:03.386 --> 01:02:04.887
I wonder what you are to me.

01:02:08.683 --> 01:02:10.852
[in English] "Facilitate."

01:02:15.356 --> 01:02:16.733
[in Korean] It's the word

01:02:17.942 --> 01:02:20.319
<i>you memorized all summer</i>
<i>while sighing the whole time.</i>

01:02:20.403 --> 01:02:22.071
[in English] "Facilitate."

01:02:24.073 --> 01:02:24.949
[in Korean] Yeah.

01:02:25.575 --> 01:02:26.868
I know.

01:02:26.951 --> 01:02:28.745
I know it. Don't tell me.

01:02:30.705 --> 01:02:31.706
[in English] Facili…

01:02:34.625 --> 01:02:36.127
[in Korean] To make possible.

01:02:40.131 --> 01:02:41.299
That's what I am.

01:02:47.680 --> 01:02:49.682
[slow romantic music playing]

01:03:04.113 --> 01:03:05.031
We'll have to

01:03:06.866 --> 01:03:08.159
be together forever.

01:03:28.930 --> 01:03:29.806
Let's do that.

01:03:33.935 --> 01:03:34.769
Starting now.

01:03:54.747 --> 01:03:57.667
STILL SHINING

01:04:26.404 --> 01:04:28.406
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
